\f + \fr 54:1\ft Barren Jews in captivity, or Church of the Gentiles, to which alone many of the expressions can be applied. (Calmet) --- The Gentiles were before unfruitful, as the Jews will be till towards the latter times. (Worthington)\f*
\f + \fr 54:2\ft Stakes, to receive so great a family. All the Israelites did not return, and it does not appear that many embraced their religion, as they have done that of Christ.\f*
\f + \fr 54:3\ft Left. To the north and south. Jerusalem increased. But what was it compared with the Christian establishment!\f*
\f + \fr 54:4\ft Widowhood. Thy former excesses shall be forgotten. (Calmet)\f*
\f + \fr 54:5\ft Thee. Hebrew, "Bohalaic (Haydock) shall be your Baalim," or husband, who was styled Lord, 1 Peter 3:6. Perhaps he may allude to the two wives, the synagogue and the Church, or to the idols, which should be adored no more.\f*
\f + \fr 54:6\ft Youth. This enhances her fault. God is pleased to overlook it, in the captives (chap. 50:1.) and Gentiles.\f*
\f + \fr 54:9\ft Earth. Giving him the rainbow for a sign. My covenant with the Church is equally irrevocable: she is founded on a rock, Matthew 16:18. (Calmet) --- Christ will no more abandon her than he will drown the world. Some mountains shall be moved out of their place, but she shall not. (Worthington)\f*
\f + \fr 54:11\ft Sapphires. Hebrew, "antimony," a mineral shining like silver, 4 Kings 9:30.\f*
\f + \fr 54:12\ft Bulwarks. Hebrew, windows of crystal; (Ezechiel 27:1[].; Calmet) Protestants, "of agate." (Haydock) --- All this is allegorical, like the redemption of the new Jerusalem, Apocalypse. xxi.\f*
\f + \fr 54:13\ft Lord, Christ, Jeremias 31:33., and John 6:45.\f*
\f + \fr 54:14\ft Thee. The Cutheans rendered the Jews suspected, 1 Esdras 4:2., and 6:1\f*
\f + \fr 54:15\ft To thee, in the inheritance. This was verified in the Church. We have no accout of many being converted before.\f*
\f + \fr 54:16\ft Destroy. I can give peace or war. (Calmet) --- Septuagint, "but I have created thee not for utter destruction." (Haydock)\f*
