\f + \fr 58:1\ft Sins. During the captivity, ver. 11. (St. Thomas Aquinas) --- Some will not hear, and those must be rebuked with all patience, till they follow virtue. (Worthington)\f*
\f + \fr 58:2\ft Approach, and contend with God, scrutinizing his conduct, (Proverbs 25:27.) and doing good for the sake of applause and self-interest.\f*
\f + \fr 58:3\ft Will. This alone suggested their fasts, and they did not shew compassion, Ezechiel 7:2. (Calmet) --- Debtors, who are not able to pay. (St. Jerome) (Deuteronomy 24:12.)\f*
\f + \fr 58:4\ft Strife. The usual works were interrupted. The Church formerly forbade law-suits on fast-days. --- Fist. Matthew 18:28. --- Wickedly. Septuagint, "the humble."\f*
\f + \fr 58:5\ft Circle. They affected extreme debility, Matthew 6:16. (Calmet) --- Ashes. These external marks of penance are not condemned, but the want of corresponding sentiments. (Haydock) --- Protestants would hence infer that fasting from flesh is not requisite, or a religious worship. But St. Jerome shews the contrary, provided it be joined with the observance of other commandments, as the saints and Christ himself have shewn us. (Worthington)\f*
\f + \fr 58:6\ft Bands. Contracts of usury, etc. (Calmet)\f*
\f + \fr 58:7\ft Deal. Literally, "break." (Haydock) --- Thin cakes are still used in the East. --- Flesh, or relation, Genesis 37:27.\f*
\f + \fr 58:8\ft Light. Prosperity, (Calmet) or Saviour. (Haydock) --- Matthew 4:2., and John 1:8. (Calmet) --- Health. Aquila, "the scar of thy wound shall soon be covered." (St. Jerome) --- Up. He shall close the rear, like the angel in the cloud, Exodus 13:21., and 14:19. He will grant thee rest from bondage in the grave and in heaven. (Calmet)\f*
\f + \fr 58:9\ft Finger, contemptuously, or threatening. (St. Jerome) --- Some explain it of the ordaining sacred ministers, or taking another's property.\f*
\f + \fr 58:10\ft Soul, effectually, and with love relieving the distressed. (Calmet)\f*
\f + \fr 58:11\ft Fail. Alexandrian Septuagint adds, "and thy bones as a flower shall spring and grow fat, and shall inherit ages of ages." St. Jerome says this is not in the best copies. (Haydock)\f*
\f + \fr 58:12\ft Generation. As the Jews did not comply with the condition, the Church falls heir to these promises.\f*
\f + \fr 58:13\ft Sabbath, doing no work, or refraining from the violation of festivals. --- Delightful. We must not think the sabbath of the Lord a loss: (Amos 8:5.) but rejoice in praising him, Psalm 45:11. (Calmet) --- A word, or to apply to God's word. (Grotius) --- Pious reading on holidays is the duty of all who have an opportunity. (Haydock)\f*
\f + \fr 58:14\ft Earth. Judea. (Calmet) --- Septuagint, "upon the good things of the land." (Haydock)\f*
